01:10:56.839 --> 01:10:58.240
A question I had,

01:10:58.240 --> 01:11:00.319
and I'm not even sure if I'm framing this the right way,

01:11:00.319 --> 01:11:04.560
but as you think about like what to consider

01:11:05.439 --> 01:11:08.560
as you like adjust your models or adjust the ratings,

01:11:09.520 --> 01:11:11.799
are there sometimes things that like come up

01:11:11.799 --> 01:11:15.959
that like athletes decide is the wrong thing

01:11:15.959 --> 01:11:17.879
for us to be adjusting based on

01:11:17.879 --> 01:11:20.000
versus what somebody thinks,

01:11:20.000 --> 01:11:21.120
like one person thinks,

01:11:21.120 --> 01:11:23.640
and then might sell that data.

01:11:24.919 --> 01:11:29.919
And like are there ethical considerations around that?

01:11:29.919 --> 01:11:31.640
There's definitely considerations

01:11:31.959 --> 01:11:34.600
around what you might do, how you might model things.

01:11:36.799 --> 01:11:39.680
So I would say like there's often pushback

01:11:39.680 --> 01:11:42.720
from those sort of in the industry

01:11:42.720 --> 01:11:46.319
around ratings like this for many reasons, right?

01:11:46.319 --> 01:11:47.759
As I said, we argue about the ratings.

01:11:47.759 --> 01:11:49.839
That's like the best last step of every rating system.

01:11:49.839 --> 01:11:54.839
So the thing to keep in mind as like you as the analysts,

01:11:56.560 --> 01:11:58.240
you should know the limits of what you're doing,

01:11:58.399 --> 01:12:00.200
you should know the limits of what you're doing,

01:12:00.200 --> 01:12:03.040
but also like the benefits of what you're doing.

01:12:03.040 --> 01:12:05.120
So your system is not gonna take into account

01:12:05.120 --> 01:12:06.080
everything a player does.

01:12:06.080 --> 01:12:08.399
It's not comprehensive, et cetera.

01:12:08.399 --> 01:12:10.439
It doesn't necessarily know about their motivation,

01:12:10.439 --> 01:12:12.879
though it may capture some of that based on how they play.

01:12:12.879 --> 01:12:15.160
So you don't necessarily,

01:12:15.160 --> 01:12:16.000
you wanna take that to the coach,

01:12:16.000 --> 01:12:17.080
like these are the best players,

01:12:17.080 --> 01:12:19.520
let's go one, two, three, four, five or whatever.

01:12:19.520 --> 01:12:20.799
It's one area.

01:12:20.799 --> 01:12:23.279
And then also listen about how they think about these things

01:12:23.279 --> 01:12:25.759
and also study your statistics,

01:12:25.759 --> 01:12:27.359
which trends year over year.

01:12:27.399 --> 01:12:29.799
Here, I just measured stuff.

01:12:29.799 --> 01:12:30.640
I didn't say like,

01:12:30.640 --> 01:12:32.359
does this correlate really strongly year over year

01:12:32.359 --> 01:12:33.200
or things like that.

01:12:33.200 --> 01:12:35.560
Those are really good analyses to do.

01:12:35.560 --> 01:12:37.799
And then if you're ever gonna like present a player

01:12:37.799 --> 01:12:39.279
or something, be careful.

01:12:39.279 --> 01:12:41.959
How would you like it if someone evaluated you

01:12:41.959 --> 01:12:45.160
based on every single action you took in our studio

01:12:45.160 --> 01:12:47.120
and the BigQuery console, for example?

